    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe text may remain in certain languages.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`short.txt`:\n```\n123\n123\n123\n```\n\n`long.txt`:\n```\n123456‡§õ‡•ã‡§°‡•ç‡§®‡•Å‡§π‡•ã‡§∏‡•ç\n123456 ‡≤¶‡≤æ‡≤ü‡≤ø\n123456 |\n```\n\n```\nnvim -u NONE\n:e long.txt\n:e short.txt\n```\n\nDisplay the following content:\n\n<img width=\"264\" height=\"182\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c290ea48-8e41-4656-a2a7-fc57c2364b62\" />\n\nThe issue exists from a897cc1 to the latest a08aa77e.\nSometimes the `|` on the third line also remains, but I couldn‚Äôt reproduce it successfully. It might be caused by the same reason as the first two lines.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDisplay the following content:\n```\n123\n123\n123\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-a08aa77e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 20.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.36.2 using VTE 0.60.3 +BIDI +GNUTLS +ICU +SYSTEMD\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
